     <span class="dvc">
      <var>x</var>
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      <var>d</var>
      <sub>xb</sub>
     </span>
     =
     <span class="dvc">
      1.39
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      11.6
     </span>
     = 0.119
    </span>
   </p>
   <p>
    Lever arm of internal forces -
    <span class="eq">
     <var>z</var>
     =
     <var>d</var>
     <sub>xb</sub>
     − 0.5 ·
     <var>λ</var>
     ·
     <var>x</var>
     = 11.6 − 0.5 · 0.8 · 1.39 = 11.05
    </span>
    cm
   </p>
   <p>
    Area of required reinforcement -
    <span class="eq">
     <var>A</var>
     <sub>sxb</sub>
     =
     <span class="dvc">
      <var>M</var>
      <sub>Ed_xb</sub>
      · 10
      <sup>3</sup>
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      <var>z</var>
      ·
      <var>f</var>
      <sub>yd</sub>
     </span>
     =
     <span class="dvc">
      17.34 · 10
      <sup>3</sup>
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      11.05 · 434.78
     </span>
     = 3.61
    </span>
    cm²/m
   </p>
   <p>
    Reinforcement ratio -
    <span class="eq">
     <var>ρ</var>
     <sub>xb</sub>
     =
     <span class="dvc">
      <var>A</var>
      <sub>sxb</sub>
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      <var>d</var>
      <sub>xb</sub>
      · 100
     </span>
     =
     <span class="dvc">
      3.61
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      11.6 · 100
     </span>
     = 0.00311
    </span>
   </p>
   <p>
    <b>The rest of the reinforcement is calculated similarly.</b>
   </p>
  </div>
  <div class="fold">
