      0.26 · 2.56
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      500
     </span>
     ; 0.0013
     <span class="b1">)</span>
     = 0.00133
    </span>
   </p>
   <p class="ref">[EN 1992-1-1, §. 9.2.1.1 (3)]</p>
   <p>
    Maximum reinforcement ratio -
    <span class="eq">
     <var>ρ</var>
     <sub>max</sub>
     = 0.04
    </span>
   </p>
   <p>Required bar spacing</p>
   <p>
    <span class="eq">
     <var>s</var>
     <sub>xb</sub>
     =
     <b>floor</b>
     <span class="b1">(</span>
     <span class="dvc">
      <var>π</var>
      ·
      <var>d</var>
      <sub>bxb</sub>
      <sup>2</sup>
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      4 ·
      <var>A</var>
      <sub>sxb</sub>
     </span>
     <span class="b1">)</span>
     =
     <b>floor</b>
     <span class="b1">(</span>
     <span class="dvc">
      3.14 · 8
      <sup>2</sup>
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      4 · 3.61
     </span>
     <span class="b1">)</span>
     = 13
    </span>
    cm
   </p>
   <p class="ref">[EN 1992-1-1, §. 9.3.1.1 (3)]</p>
   <p>Maximum bar spacing</p>
   <p>
    <span class="eq">
     <var>s</var>
     <sub>max</sub>
     =
     <b>min</b>
     ( 2 ·
     <var>h</var>
     ; 25 )  =
     <b>min</b>
     ( 2 · 14; 25 )  = 25
    </span>
    cm
   </p>
   <p>
    <b>The rest of the reinforcement is detailed similarly.</b>
